Title : Portal:Current events/2014 May 2
Text : <!-- All news items below this line -->{{Current events header|2014|05|02}}

;Armed conflicts and attacks
*[[Syrian Civil War]] ([[Siege of Homs]]):
**A 24-hour ceasefire deal is reached in Syria's city of [[Homs]] allowing rebels to withdraw from their last stronghold in the central city. [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-27252396 (BBC)] [https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/05/02/us-syria-crisis-homs-idUSBREA410CA20140502 (Reuters)]
*[[Post-coup unrest in Egypt (2013–14)|Post-coup unrest in Egypt]] ([[Sinai insurgency]]):
**Attacks by suicide bombers on a security checkpoint and a civilian bus in [[Egypt]]’s [[Sinai Peninsula]] as well as a separate bombing near a courthouse in [[Cairo]] killed at least four people. [https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/egypt-suicide-bombers-hit-in-sinai-kill-soldier/2014/05/02/af05d932-d1ba-11e3-a714-be7e7f142085_story.html (The Washington Post)] 
**Two people were shot dead when supporters of deposed President [[Mohamed Morsi]] clashed with residents in [[Alexandria]]. [http://uk.reuters.com/article/2014/05/02/uk-egypt-violence-idUKKBN0DI07A20140502 (Reuters)]
*At least nine students are killed in protests in [[Ethiopia]]'s [[Oromia Region]]. [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-27251331 (BBC)]
*Security tightens in the [[People's Republic of China]] after [[April 2014 Ürümqi attack|Wednesday's bombing]] at a train station left three dead and 79 injured. [http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2617196/Three-die-scores-injured-terrorist-blast-train-station-Chinas-far-west.html (Daily Mail)]
*[[2014 pro-Russian unrest in Ukraine]] and the [[Siege of Sloviansk]]
**The [[Armed Forces of Ukraine]] launch a military operation against separatists in the city of [[Sloviansk]] with claims of many deaths and two Ukrainian Army helicopters downed. In the port city of [[Odessa]], violent clashes kill at least 42 people, as pro-Ukrainians set the pro-Russian headquarters on fire. [http://edition.cnn.com/2014/05/02/world/europe/ukraine-crisis/index.html (CNN)], [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-27259614# (BBC)], [http://www.express.co.uk/news/world/473754/Dozens-killed-by-smoke-as-Ukraine-moves-closer-to-civil-war (Express)]

;Disasters and accidents
*A landslide strikes the town of Hobo Barik in [[Afghanistan]]'s [[Badakhshan]] province with at least 350 people dead and over 2000 people missing. [https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2014/05/02/afghanistan-landslide/8607051/ (USA Today)], [http://hosted2.ap.org/APDEFAULT/3d281c11a96b4ad082fe88aa0db04305/Article_2014-05-02-Afghanistan-Landslide/id-a12d2e538369414fbad43e4af30ad96a (AP)]

;Law and crime
*[[Murder of Jean McConville]] and [[Arrest of Gerry Adams]]:
**[[Sinn Féin]] claims that party president [[Gerry Adams]] is a victim of "political policing" are dismissed by the Taoiseach (Prime Minister of Ireland) [[Enda Kenny]], British prime minister [[David Cameron]] and Northern Ireland First Minister [[Peter Robinson (Northern Ireland politician)|Peter Robinson]]. [http://www.irishtimes.com/news/crime-and-law/gerry-adams-spends-second-night-in-police-custody-1.1781456 (''Irish Times'')]
**Helen, the eldest daughter of [[Provisional Irish Republican Army]] (IRA) murder victim Jean McConville, is prepared to name the people responsible for her mother's death, saying she no longer fears reprisals by republicans. [http://www.rte.ie/news/2014/0501/614157-adams-mcconville/ (RTE News)]

